OL,7,FThe sentences were initially intended
OL,8,Fto be handed to the most serious
OL,9,Foffenders whose crimes did not warrant
OL,10,Fa life sentence, with the view that
OL,11,Fthey would only be released once re-
OL,12,Fhabilitated.
OL,14,FBut once released from custody,
OL,15,Foffenders remain on licence for an
OL,16,Findefinite period meaning they can be
OL,17,Frecalled at any time, often for
OL,18,Fbehaviour which is not deemed criminal.
