OL,7,FNow, as a bill to allow re-sentencing
OL,8,Fof all IPP offenders progresses
OL,9,Fthrough the House of Lords, people who
OL,10,Fare living with IPP conditions have
OL,11,Fsaid they are the equivalent to a life
OL,12,Fsentence.
OL,14,FShaun Lloyd was originally sentenced
OL,15,Fto two and a half years in prison in
OL,16,F2005 after stealing a mobile phone,
OL,17,Fbut spent nine consecutive years
OL,18,Fbehind bars. He is now currently back
OL,19,Fin prison after being recalled on his
OL,20,FIPP in March 2024.
