OL,4,Cdubbed 'inhumane' 20 years after
OL,5,Ccoming in
OL,7,FLord Blunkett said: "Whilst parliament
OL,8,Fagreed to the imprisonment for public
OL,9,Fprotection sentence all those years
OL,10,Fago without dissent, no one `
OL,11,Fincluding me - envisaged that
OL,12,Fprisoners would be held for so long,
OL,13,Fand have such difficulty in gaining
OL,14,Fagreement to the Parole Board
OL,15,Freleasing them back into the
OL,16,Fcommunity. That is why a group of
OL,17,Fpeers have been working with a range
OL,18,Fof charities and organisations to make
OL,19,Freal progress including legislation,
OL,20,Fthis time last year, which has seen
OL,21,F1,800 former prisoners have their
OL,22,Flicense conditions lifted.
